headline: Mag 7, tech weakness is breeding new opportunities: Where to look
summary: Meta Platforms (META) has erased its year-to-date gains, making it the final component of the Magnificent Seven group of tech stocks to turn negative in 2025. Where exactly are investors finding new opportunities as this might be a signal for them to pivot away from Big Tech? Aptus Capital Advisors portfolio manager David Wagner underlines the push to diversify into small-cap stocks, while naming some alternatives to mega-cap tech names in other sectors. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Wealth here.

headline: 2 Large-Cap Stocks on Our Buy List and 1 to Brush Off
summary: Large-cap stocks have the power to shape entire industries thanks to their size and widespread influence. With such vast footprints, however, finding new areas for growth is much harder than for smaller, more agile players.
